                <div class="penno-avobilam-container1">
                    <h1 class="penno-avobilam-heading mt-2">Puttaparthi Sai Baba</h1>
                    <p class="penno-avobilam-description">Puttaparthi Sai Baba, born as Sathyanarayana Raju in 1926, was a prominent spiritual leader who gained worldwide recognition. At a young age, he proclaimed himself as the reincarnation of Sai Baba of Shirdi. He started attracting followers and began spreading his teachings of love, service, and spiritual upliftment. Sai Baba established the Sri Sathya Sai Organization, which focused on providing education, healthcare, and social welfare services to the underprivileged. His ashram in Puttaparthi, Prasanthi Nilayam, became a center of spiritual learning and devotion. Sai Baba's reputation grew due to his reported miracles, healing abilities, and profound wisdom. He gained a massive following and touched the lives of millions through his teachings and philanthropic work until his passing in 2011.</p>
