                <div class="penno-avobilam-container1">
                    <h1 class="penno-avobilam-heading mt-2">Thimmamma Marrimanu</h1>
                    <p class="penno-avobilam-description">Thimmamma Marrimanu, located in Anantapur district of Andhra Pradesh, is considered the largest banyan tree in the world. It is named after Thimmamma, a local woman who sacrificed her life for her husband's well-being. The tree is estimated to be over 550 years old and covers an extensive area. It has a sprawling canopy with numerous aerial roots that descend from its branches and form new trunks. Thimmamma Marrimanu holds great cultural and religious significance and is visited by pilgrims and tourists alike. It is a natural wonder and a testament to the resilience and beauty of nature. Efforts have been made to preserve and protect this remarkable tree for future generations to marvel at its grandeur.
                    </p>
                </div>
